The Olubadan of Ibadanland, His Imperial Majesty, Oba Saliu Adetunji, has described the late Olowo of Owo, Oba Olateru Olagbegi as a great man, even in death. In a statement issued by his Director of Media,  Adeola Oloko on Wednesday, Oba Adetunji while reacting to the death of the monarch pointed out that the death of Olowo came as a rude shock to him but noted that he lived an exemplary life worthy of emulation. Olubadan however commiserated with the government and people of Ondo State in general and people of Owo town and his immediate family in particular. Ajimobi, Shittu commiserate with Olubadan on wife’s death A visit to Owo Ondo traditional ruler, Olowo of Owo dies at 77